==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: big band
<hw>big band</hw>, <def>A band that is the size of an orchestra, usually
playing mostly jazz or swing music. The <ex>big band</ex> typically
features both ensemble and solo playing, sometimes has a lead singer,
and is often located in a night club where the patrons may dance to its
music. The <ex>big bands</ex> were popular from the late 1920's to the
1940's. Contrasted with <er>combo</er>, which has fewer
players.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>big bang</ent>⟦br⟧
